{"lemma":"حَفَظَة","slug":"حَفَظَة","root":"ح.ف.ظ","root_slug":"ح-ف-ظ","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ف-ظ","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حافِظ","root":"حفظ","pos":"N","occurrence_count":13},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["name","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8497","n8504"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B8%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to preserve, to maintain, to keep up, to uphold, to sustain"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to supervise, to control, to watch over, to watch out for"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to take care, to attend, to pay attention"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to keep, to follow, to observe, to comply, to conform"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to protect, to guard, to defend"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"guard, guardian, keeper, custodian, caretaker"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hafiz (one who knows the Qur'an by heart)"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name, Hafez or Hafiz"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Hafez aš-Šīrāzi, a famous mystic 14th century Persian poet, who also wrote in Arabic and whose poems are sometimes used as omens."}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of حَفِظَ (ḥafiẓa, “to guard, to keep; to memorize”), from the root ح ف ظ (ḥ f ẓ). The Persian poet was named such as he had memorised the Qurʾān."},"ipa":["/ħaː.fa.ðˤa/","/ħaː.fiðˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8497","headword_ar":"حَفِظَهُ","root":"HfZ","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HifoZu","text_ar":"حِفْظُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He kept it, preserved it, guarded it, protected it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took care of it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) namely, a thing; (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he prevented it from perishing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"becoming lost;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb;) namely, a thing, (Mgh,) or property &c.; (Msb;) and hence the saying, (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HifoZN","text_ar":"حِفْظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nisoyaAnN","text_ar":"نِسْيَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, Mgh;) i. e., it signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking  care, being careful;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being mind ful, regardful, attentive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"considerate:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) [see also 5:] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtfZ","text_ar":"احتفظ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafiZahu","text_ar":"حَفِظَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb.) [Hence,] you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafiZa AlmaAla","text_ar":"حَفِظَ المَالَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He kept and tended,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pastured and defended, the camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafiZa Huromapa SaAHibihi","text_ar":"حَفِظَ حُرْمَةَ صَاحِبِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was regardful of everything entitled to reverence, respect, honour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defence, in the character and appertenances of his companion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"friend."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafiZa Als~ir~a","text_ar":"حَفِظَ السِّرَّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He kept the secret."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafiZa yamiynahu","text_ar":"حَفِظَ يَمِينَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He kept his oath:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this has also another meaning, as will be seen below.] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafiZa AlquroA=na","text_ar":"حَفِظَ القُرْا=نَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He kept,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"retained, the Kur-án in his mind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"memory; got it, knew it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"learned it, by heart."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Msb, K.) [See also 5.] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafiZa Eino fulaAnK","text_ar":"حَفِظَ عِنْ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He learned by heart from such a one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and, followed by an accus. case, the same; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he retained in his memory, as learned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heard, from such a one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he remembered to have heard from such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA &c. passim.) And one says of God,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado HafiZa EalaY xaloqihi waEibaAdihi maA yaEomaluwna","text_ar":"قَدْ حَفِظَ عَلَى خَلْقِهِ وَعِبَادِهِ مَا يَعْمَلُونَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino xayorK A^awo $ar~K","text_ar":"مِنْ خَيْرٍ اَوْ شَرٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hath preserved from oblivion, for,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against, his creatures and his servants, what they do of good or evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He kept it from being used,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"employed, on,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for, ordinary, mean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vile, occasions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purposes."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yaHofaZu nafosahu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يَحْفَظُ نَفْسَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walisaAnahu","text_ar":"وَلِسَانَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one keeps himself and his tongue from ordinary, mean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vile, employment, in that which does not concern him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) And hence the saying in the Kur [v. 91],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@HofaZuwA","text_ar":"وَا@حْفَظُوا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayomaAnakumo","text_ar":"اَيْمَانَكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to one of the modes of interpreting it; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And keep ye your oaths from being used,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uttered, on,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for, ordinary, mean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vile, occasions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purposes;"},{"kind":"text","text":"agreeably with what is said in ii. 224 of the Kur, where ordinary and frequent swearing by God is forbidden. (Mgh.) [Another meaning of which this phrase is susceptible has been shown above.]"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","M"]},{"entry_id":"n8504","headword_ar":"حِفْظَةٌ","root":"HfZ","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafiyZapN","text_ar":"حَفِيظَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}